00:00:01:130000.Speaker: Penny
00:00:01:130000.Dialogue: Hey, you guys ready to order?

00:00:05:130000.Speaker: Priya
00:00:05:130000.Dialogue: Uh, I'll have the shepherd's pie. You want to split that with me?

00:00:07:180000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:07:180000.Dialogue: Oh, no, no, no, he doesn't.

00:00:10:150000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:10:150000.Dialogue: Well, you have milk in the taters, milk in the gravy, parmesan crust. Your lactose-intolerant boyfriend will turn into a gas-filled Macy's Day balloon.

00:00:20:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:20:180000.Dialogue: Not quite accurate. The Macy's balloons are filled with helium, whereas Leonard produces copious amounts of methane.

00:00:32:090000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:32:090000.Dialogue: So, no, on the shepherd's pie. Can we move on?

00:00:34:190000.Speaker: Penny
00:00:34:190000.Dialogue: Yeah, a little tip: he says he can eat frozen yogurt. Do not believe it.

00:00:39:040000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:39:040000.Dialogue: Sea bass! I'll have the sea bass!

00:00:41:230000.Speaker: Howard
00:00:41:230000.Dialogue: You gotta like this, the girlfriend and the ex-girlfriend bonding over your rooty-tooty stinky booty.

00:00:50:150000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:50:150000.Dialogue: It wouldn'help. The human body is capable of being flatulent for hours after death.

00:01:01:030000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:01:01:030000.Dialogue: Guys, sorry I'm late. I have amazing news.

00:01:03:130000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:03:130000.Dialogue: Bernadette, before you change the subject, does anyone have any final comments on Leonard's faulty digestive system?

00:01:11:140000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:01:11:140000.Dialogue: The thesis committee accepted my doctoral dissertation. I'm getting my PhD!

00:01:20:190000.Speaker: Penny
00:01:20:190000.Dialogue: Wow, so that means you're a doctor, you're a doctor, you're a doctor, you're a doctor, and Howard, you know a lot of doctors.

00:01:36:060000.Speaker: Leonard
00:01:36:060000.Dialogue: So, Howard, tell us, how's it feel knowing that when you two get married, you'll be referred to as Mr. and Dr. Wolowitz?

00:01:43:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:43:100000.Dialogue: Unless he takes Bernadette's last name. And considering her advanced status, that could open some doors for him.

00:01:49:070000.Speaker: Howard
00:01:49:070000.Dialogue: Please, this isn't about me. - I'm proud of you.

00:01:50:230000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:01:50:230000.Dialogue: - Well, you'll be really be proud of this. I was headhunted by a big pharmaceutical company. They're gonna pay me a buttload of money!

00:02:00:230000.Speaker: Leonard
00:02:00:230000.Dialogue: Bernadette, that's great. Howard, do you make a buttload?

00:02:04:160000.Speaker: Howard
00:02:04:160000.Dialogue: Better than what you've got a buttload of.

00:02:11:040000.Speaker: Leonard
00:02:11:040000.Dialogue: Hey, if I roll down the windows in the car, everything's peachy. If you do it, you're still not a doctor.

00:02:17:130000.Speaker: Penny
00:02:17:130000.Dialogue: Yeah, just a heads-up on the car window deal. It helps, but everything is not "peachy. "

00:03:02:200000.Speaker: Priya
00:03:02:200000.Dialogue: PRIYA: Oh, God, I feel ridiculous in this dress.

00:03:05:030000.Speaker: Leonard
00:03:05:030000.Dialogue: LEONARD: You look beautiful, Lieutenant Uhura. (a la Capt. Kirk): Now prepare for... inspection.

00:03:14:030000.Speaker: Priya
00:03:14:030000.Dialogue: PRIYA: Shh, my brother's going to hear you.

00:03:16:060000.Speaker: Leonard
00:03:16:060000.Dialogue: LEONARD: Relax, he's got headphones on. And we're ten miles above Earth in a starship.

00:03:21:060000.Speaker: Raj
00:03:21:060000.Dialogue: Really, ten miles? You're orbiting inside the atmosphere? Moron.

00:03:26:120000.Speaker: Priya
00:03:26:120000.Dialogue: PRIYA: I can't believe I'm wearing my brother's Halloween costume.

00:03:30:220000.Speaker: Leonard
00:03:30:220000.Dialogue: LEONARD: I can't believe you think he only wears it on Halloween.

00:03:35:200000.Speaker: Leonard
00:03:35:200000.Dialogue: Open the landing bay doors, shuttle craft approaching.

00:03:48:150000.Speaker: Mrs Wolowitz
00:03:48:150000.Dialogue: MRS. WOLOWITZ: Is that my future daughter-in-law, the doctor?!

00:04:01:110000.Speaker: Mrs Wolowitz
00:04:01:110000.Dialogue: Like Leonard and the skinny weirdo!

00:04:05:190000.Speaker: Howard
00:04:05:190000.Dialogue: Sheldon, yes! Everybody's a doctor but me!

00:04:15:230000.Speaker: Raj
00:04:15:230000.Dialogue: Leonard's putting disgusting memories in my memory foam mattress. Can I stay here tonight?

00:04:22:140000.Speaker: Howard
00:04:22:140000.Dialogue: Sure, but I'm going out with Bernadette. It'll just be you and my mother.

00:04:32:010000.Speaker: Mrs Wolowitz
00:04:32:010000.Dialogue: Of course, he and I can play doctor!

00:04:40:160000.Speaker: Howard
00:04:40:160000.Dialogue: I don't know, she's pretty feisty since they put her on hormone-replacement therapy.

00:04:52:150000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is talking to Amy on webcam.
00:04:52:150000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:52:150000.Dialogue: I must say, Amy, I was very impressed to see that Bernadette got her PhD.

00:04:57:150000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is talking to Amy on webcam.
00:04:57:150000.Speaker: Amy
00:04:57:150000.Dialogue: It's indeed admirable. Although, it is... microbiology.

00:05:02:040000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is talking to Amy on webcam.
00:05:02:040000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:02:040000.Dialogue: Your doctorate is in neurobiology. I fail to see the distinction.

00:05:07:230000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is talking to Amy on webcam.
00:05:07:230000.Speaker: Amy
00:05:07:230000.Dialogue: I'll make it simple for you. I study the brain, the organ responsible for Beethoven's Fifth Symphony. Bernadette studies yeast, the organism responsible for Michelob Lite.

00:05:18:230000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is talking to Amy on webcam.
00:05:18:230000.Speaker: Amy
00:05:18:230000.Dialogue: Is there something wrong with your neck?

00:05:20:210000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is talking to Amy on webcam.
00:05:20:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:20:210000.Dialogue: It's a little stiff. What a remarkably fragile structure to support such a valuable payload. Not unlike balancing a Faberge egg on a Pixie Stick.

00:05:33:130000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is talking to Amy on webcam.
00:05:33:130000.Speaker: Amy

00:05:35:090000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is talking to Amy on webcam.
00:05:35:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:35:090000.Dialogue: I'd like to respond to that sarcastically: Yes, I relish the thought of a stranger covering my body with oil and rubbing it.

00:05:43:150000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is talking to Amy on webcam.
00:05:43:150000.Speaker: Amy
00:05:43:150000.Dialogue: I was proposing you massage your muscles with your own hands.

00:05:47:120000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is talking to Amy on webcam.
00:05:47:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:47:120000.Dialogue: Still sounds like a lot of unnecessary touching.

00:05:50:220000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is talking to Amy on webcam.
00:05:50:220000.Speaker: Amy
00:05:50:220000.Dialogue: Trust me. With your right hand, locate the spot where the scapula meets the acromion process.

00:05:58:210000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is talking to Amy on webcam.
00:05:58:210000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:06:00:160000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is talking to Amy on webcam.
00:06:00:160000.Speaker: Amy
00:06:00:160000.Dialogue: Now push your third finger along the ridge of the shoulder blade, making a small rotation as you do so.

00:06:04:120000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is talking to Amy on webcam.
00:06:04:120000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:06:08:020000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is talking to Amy on webcam.
00:06:08:020000.Speaker: Amy
00:06:08:020000.Dialogue: You should feel a small node-like object rolling back and forth along the bone.

00:06:11:160000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is talking to Amy on webcam.
00:06:11:160000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:06:13:190000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is talking to Amy on webcam.
00:06:13:190000.Speaker: Amy
00:06:13:190000.Dialogue: Obviously. Now bear down on it like the seventh grade noogies we all know too well.

00:06:23:040000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is talking to Amy on webcam.
00:06:23:040000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:06:23:040000.Dialogue: Oh, dear Lord, yes, yes, oh, yes!

00:06:28:210000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is talking to Amy on webcam.
00:06:28:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:06:28:210000.Dialogue: Amy, I've never been touched like this before!

00:06:33:060000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is talking to Amy on webcam.
00:06:33:060000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:06:37:000000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is talking to Amy on webcam.
00:06:37:000000.Speaker: Amy
00:06:37:000000.Dialogue: Don't flatter yourself. Your hands are blunt tools guided by my knowledge of the nervous system. I could just as easily have paralyzed you.

00:06:47:120000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is talking to Amy on webcam.
00:06:47:120000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:06:49:190000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is talking to Amy on webcam.
00:06:49:190000.Speaker: Amy

00:06:56:200000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is talking to Amy on webcam.
00:06:56:200000.Speaker: Raj

00:06:58:170000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is talking to Amy on webcam.
00:06:58:170000.Speaker: Raj
00:06:58:170000.Dialogue: - Leonard's having astronomically inaccurate Star Trek sex with my sister.

00:07:04:110000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is talking to Amy on webcam.
00:07:04:110000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:04:110000.Dialogue: I can see how that would be upsetting. Come in.

00:07:08:020000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is talking to Amy on webcam.
00:07:08:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:08:020000.Dialogue: I'll gethe sheets and blankets for the couch.

00:07:10:020000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is talking to Amy on webcam.
00:07:10:020000.Speaker: Raj
00:07:10:020000.Dialogue: Oh, don't bother. I'll just sleep in Leonard's room.

00:07:12:110000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is talking to Amy on webcam.
00:07:12:110000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:07:14:010000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is talking to Amy on webcam.
00:07:14:010000.Speaker: Raj
00:07:14:010000.Dialogue: Well, he's in my bed. Why can't I be in his?

00:07:16:210000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is talking to Amy on webcam.
00:07:16:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:16:210000.Dialogue: The Hammurabic Code is "an eye for an eye," not "a bed for a bed. "

00:07:21:110000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is talking to Amy on webcam.
00:07:21:110000.Speaker: Raj
00:07:21:110000.Dialogue: Come on, dude, I'm exhausted, and Tyra Banks says the most important item in your makeup bag is a good night's sleep.

00:07:31:150000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is talking to Amy on webcam.
00:07:31:150000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:07:33:040000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is talking to Amy on webcam.
00:07:33:040000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:33:040000.Dialogue: This is a form indemnifying me

00:07:36:160000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is talking to Amy on webcam.
00:07:36:160000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:36:160000.Dialogue: from your use of "Leonard's bedroom. " Sign here, indicating that I tried to stop you and did so using a stern facial expression.

00:07:50:170000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is talking to Amy on webcam.
00:07:50:170000.Speaker: Raj

00:07:52:090000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is talking to Amy on webcam.
00:07:52:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:52:090000.Dialogue: Wait. Not yet. We still have to go over safety procedures. Now, the apartment has three emergency exits located here, here, and here. In the event of a power outage, luminous paint will guide you to the nearest exit.

00:08:05:210000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is talking to Amy on webcam.
00:08:05:210000.Speaker: Raj

00:08:16:180000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. Leonard enters, and accidentally sits on Raj. Both exclaim.
00:08:16:180000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:08:19:000000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. Leonard enters, and accidentally sits on Raj. Both exclaim.

00:08:30:210000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. Leonard enters, and accidentally sits on Raj. Both exclaim.
00:08:30:210000.Speaker: Leonard

00:08:33:200000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. Leonard enters, and accidentally sits on Raj. Both exclaim.
00:08:33:200000.Speaker: Raj

00:08:35:040000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. Leonard enters, and accidentally sits on Raj. Both exclaim.
00:08:35:040000.Speaker: Leonard

00:08:36:090000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. Leonard enters, and accidentally sits on Raj. Both exclaim.
00:08:36:090000.Speaker: Raj
00:08:36:090000.Dialogue: Well, I would've slept in my own bed, but it was being used to bring shame to my family.

00:08:41:070000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. Leonard enters, and accidentally sits on Raj. Both exclaim.
00:08:41:070000.Speaker: Raj
00:08:41:070000.Dialogue: And the memory of Gene Roddenberry.

00:08:44:210000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. Leonard enters, and accidentally sits on Raj. Both exclaim.
00:08:44:210000.Speaker: Leonard

00:08:46:110000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. Leonard enters, and accidentally sits on Raj. Both exclaim.
00:08:46:110000.Speaker: Raj

00:08:50:090000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. Leonard enters, and accidentally sits on Raj. Both exclaim.
00:08:50:090000.Speaker: Leonard
00:08:50:090000.Dialogue: Sorry. Does Sheldon know you're sleeping in here?

00:08:53:160000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. Leonard enters, and accidentally sits on Raj. Both exclaim.
00:08:53:160000.Speaker: Raj
00:08:53:160000.Dialogue: Are you kidding? He made me sign a waiver, participate in an emergency fire drill and take a refresher course in CPR. Thank God he had a dummy.

00:09:03:130000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. Leonard enters, and accidentally sits on Raj. Both exclaim.
00:09:03:130000.Speaker: Leonard
00:09:03:130000.Dialogue: Oh, yeah. Mouth-to-Mouth Mona. You know, she used to date Howard?

00:09:09:050000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. Leonard enters, and accidentally sits on Raj. Both exclaim.
00:09:09:050000.Speaker: Raj
00:09:09:050000.Dialogue: Oh, my God, she's that Mona? Why can't you and my sister spend your nights here?

00:09:16:020000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. Leonard enters, and accidentally sits on Raj. Both exclaim.
00:09:16:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:09:16:020000.Dialogue: We tried. She doesn't get along with Sheldon.

00:09:18:050000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. Leonard enters, and accidentally sits on Raj. Both exclaim.
00:09:18:050000.Speaker: Raj
00:09:18:050000.Dialogue: Sheldon doesn't get along with Sheldon. It's still no reason for me to have to listen to you arm your photon torpedoes every night.

00:09:26:040000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. Leonard enters, and accidentally sits on Raj. Both exclaim.
00:09:26:040000.Speaker: Leonard
00:09:26:040000.Dialogue: Okay, well, how about this: until Priya gets her own place, you stay here and I'll stay at your apartment.

00:09:31:180000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. Leonard enters, and accidentally sits on Raj. Both exclaim.
00:09:31:180000.Speaker: Raj

00:09:35:160000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. Leonard enters, and accidentally sits on Raj. Both exclaim.
00:09:35:160000.Speaker: Leonard
00:09:35:160000.Dialogue: You? Sure. Bring as many as you want.

00:09:40:060000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. Leonard enters, and accidentally sits on Raj. Both exclaim.
00:09:40:060000.Speaker: Raj

00:09:45:070000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. Leonard enters, and accidentally sits on Raj. Both exclaim.
00:09:45:070000.Speaker: Leonard

00:09:52:210000.Speaker: Leonard
00:09:52:210000.Dialogue: Do you really think you should be eating that cake?

00:09:55:130000.Speaker: Leonard
00:09:55:130000.Dialogue: If you're gonna be a trophy husband for a rich wife, you might want to watch your waistline.

00:10:01:020000.Speaker: Raj
00:10:01:020000.Dialogue: He's right. A minute on the lips, a lifetime on the hips.

00:10:05:070000.Speaker: Howard
00:10:05:070000.Dialogue: Yeah, ha-ha. First of all, I'm not threatened by my fiancée's success. I'm proud of her. And secondly, I have my own career.

00:10:17:150000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:17:150000.Dialogue: Good news, Raj. I got the blood work back from the lab. You're okay to stay for a while.

00:10:23:230000.Speaker: Raj
00:10:23:230000.Dialogue: When did you take my blood?

00:10:25:130000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:25:130000.Dialogue: Not important. Your sugar was a little high. I'd follow up with your regular physician. In the meantime, I have some paperwork here for you to go over.

00:10:37:050000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:37:050000.Dialogue: Boilerplate stuff. A modified roommate agreement for a temporary house guest. And a living will and durable power of attorney.

00:10:46:070000.Speaker: Raj
00:10:46:070000.Dialogue: This says you can make "end of life" decisions for me.

00:10:50:130000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:50:130000.Dialogue: As your friend, let's hope it doesn't come to that. Please sign.

00:10:56:140000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:56:140000.Dialogue: There's a reciprocity clause. You get to pull the plug on him, too.

00:11:04:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:04:070000.Dialogue: Congratulations and welcome temporarily aboard. Here's your I.D. card, your key and your lapel pin. Which Leonard was too cool to wear.

00:11:21:010000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:21:010000.Dialogue: FYI, part of your responsibilities as roommate pro tem will be to drive me to and from work, the comic book store, the barbershop and the park for one hour every other Sunday for fresh air.

00:11:32:150000.Speaker: Leonard
00:11:32:150000.Dialogue: Bring a ball or a Frisbee, you know, something he can chase.

00:11:37:130000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:37:130000.Dialogue: Also, you're tasked with bringing home all takeout dinners. Tonight is Thai food. You'll find the standard order in appendix B or downloadable from my FTP server. If you have any questions, here's the FAQ sheet, or if you prefer the human touch, I do a live web chat called "Apartment Talk" on Tuesday nights.

00:12:17:230000.Speaker: Raj
00:12:17:230000.Dialogue: This is the difference between eating and dining.

00:12:25:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:25:170000.Dialogue: Remarkable. I'm just realizing how much Leonard's been skating by all these years.

00:12:34:100000.Speaker: Raj
00:12:34:100000.Dialogue: It's not a big thing. Just think of me as a brown Martha Stewart.

00:12:41:080000.Speaker: Penny
00:12:41:080000.Dialogue: Hey, Sheldon, did you change your Wi-Fi password again?

00:12:43:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:43:230000.Dialogue: Yes, it's "Penny, get your own Wi-Fi. " No spaces.

00:12:47:130000.Speaker: Penny
00:12:47:130000.Dialogue: Thanks. Wow! What's with the fancy spread?

00:12:51:130000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:51:130000.Dialogue: My new roommate is bending over backwards to ingratiate himself to me. Uh, nice touch, by the way.

00:13:00:040000.Speaker: Penny
00:13:00:040000.Dialogue: What do you mean "new roommate"? What happened to Leonard?

00:13:02:080000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:02:080000.Dialogue: The same thing that happened to Homo erectus. He was replaced by a superior species.

00:13:08:090000.Speaker: Raj
00:13:08:090000.Dialogue: I'm the new Homo in town.

00:13:15:160000.Speaker: Penny
00:13:15:160000.Dialogue: All right, let me try this again. Where's Leonard?

00:13:18:040000.Speaker: Raj
00:13:18:040000.Dialogue: He's living at my place, so I'm living here.

00:13:20:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:20:120000.Dialogue: You're living here provisionally. But I must say it's looking good.

00:13:24:230000.Speaker: Penny
00:13:24:230000.Dialogue: Wow Leonard and Priya are living together? That's big.

00:13:29:010000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:29:010000.Dialogue: No. Origami napkin swans... that's the headline.

00:13:41:040000.Speaker: Howard
00:13:41:040000.Dialogue: So do you know what kind of research you'll be doing at this pharmaceutical company?

00:13:45:170000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:13:45:170000.Dialogue: Well, there are a couple of opportunities available, but I volunteered for the premature ejaculation project.

00:13:56:070000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:13:56:070000.Dialogue: I mean, it's not like either one of us has heart disease.

00:14:04:020000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:14:04:020000.Dialogue: Oh, I almost forgot. I got you a little present.

00:14:06:200000.Speaker: Howard
00:14:06:200000.Dialogue: Oh, Bernie, no. You didn't have to.

00:14:09:140000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:14:09:140000.Dialogue: I wanted to. Come on, open it.

00:14:14:110000.Speaker: Howard
00:14:14:110000.Dialogue: You bought me a Rolex? How much did this cost?

00:14:20:140000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:14:20:140000.Dialogue: Oh, you let me worry about the money.

00:14:24:230000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:14:24:230000.Dialogue: I just want my baby to have pretty things.

00:14:34:070000.Speaker: Penny
00:14:34:070000.Dialogue: Oh, no, no, no. I've had way too much already.

00:14:36:150000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:36:150000.Dialogue: Here's an interesting fact about alcohol...

00:14:43:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:43:090000.Dialogue: Man is not the only species that ferments fruit in order to become intoxicated. Can you guess what the other is? Hint: sometimes they pack the alcohol in their trunks.

00:15:01:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:01:120000.Dialogue: When does a monkey have a trunk?

00:15:04:180000.Speaker: Penny
00:15:04:180000.Dialogue: When a suitcase just won't do.

00:15:10:130000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:10:130000.Dialogue: Mmm, all right. It would appear as if alcohol is playing keep-away with your intelligence. Good night. Please note, it is now past 10:00 p. m. Per our roommate agreement, kindly refrain from raucous laughter, clinking of glasses, and celebratory gunfire.

00:15:30:190000.Speaker: Penny
00:15:30:190000.Dialogue: Okay... (clears throat) explain something to me. You watch Leonard put up with that guy for years and years. What has to break inside your brain for you to think, (with Indian accent): "Oh, Krishna, I've got to get me some of that"?

00:15:44:170000.Speaker: Raj
00:15:44:170000.Dialogue: Well, it's a lot better than having to wear noise-cancelling headphones in my own apartment.

00:15:49:040000.Speaker: Penny
00:15:49:040000.Dialogue: What? Oh, God, yeah. Yeah. Leonard's a noisy little dude in the sack.

00:16:02:020000.Speaker: Raj
00:16:02:020000.Dialogue: It's my sister. Can we not talk about this anymore?

00:16:04:140000.Speaker: Penny
00:16:04:140000.Dialogue: Yeah. Sorry, sorry. Can I tell you a secret?

00:16:11:040000.Speaker: Penny
00:16:11:040000.Dialogue: I screwed up. Leonard's a great guy. Never should have broken up with him.

00:16:17:160000.Speaker: Raj
